textBeforeTable: "We didn't play well because they didn't allow us to play well. I am very happy and proud of my players that they did not give up. They didn't mentally drop. It was a big challenge and a big game to win. I will remember this one for the great play at the end by a great captain. There was also a great screen by Vorontsevich to get Monya open and he deserves a lot of credit too." Russia Head Coach David Blatt: "Firstly, congratulations to Russia for the win. With this game we again proved we deserve to go to the quarter-finals. We knew before the start of the game rebounding would be our problem as we don't have Todor Gechevski. I think we played very well in defence again but I think the Russian bench solved the problem for them again." FYR of Macedonia Head Coach Marin Dokuzovski: "It was a big shot. There was very little time to do something. It was 0.7 seconds to go and I had to act fast. I told Shved to pass me the ball, he did and I went up for the shot. it's really a great feeling.
